# Cursor Rules - AsapGuide Tools

Always follow these guidelines when editing or adding tools to prevent UI regressions, branding leaks, and build failures.

## 1. Branding & Navigation Constraints
- NEVER include links pointing to "Main Site" or the external domain `asapguide.com` in headers, footers, or layout templates.
- The tools interface must remain self-contained, focusing exclusively on the local tools utility index.

## 2. UI Aesthetics & Layout Rules (Avoid Clunky & Overcrowded UI)
- **Symmetrical Design**: Side-by-side layout grids (like comparison panels or editors) must have symmetric sub-toolbars (`.editor-toolbar`) nested inside `.input-container` rather than cluttering panel bars.
- **Panel Action Limits**: Do NOT place more than two buttons in `.panel-bar-right`. Extra controls, dropdowns, and formatting parameters must go inside the nested `.editor-toolbar`.
- **Button Sizing**: Maintain uniform compact sizing. Ghost buttons (`.btn-ghost`) and primary buttons (`.btn-primary`) in panel bars must share the same height/padding (`padding: 6px 12px; font-size: 0.8rem;`).
- **Segmented Controls**: Mutually exclusive options (e.g. modes, operating systems) must use segmented controls (`.segmented-control`), not separate raw buttons.
- **Focus Rings**: Always wrap input fields and their footer controls/bars inside a `.input-container` with `:focus-within` styling to ensure a single clean focus ring around the whole group.

## 3. Defensive Layouts & Text Wrapping
- Ensure flex items that hold dynamic titles/actions use `flex-wrap: nowrap` paired with proper min-widths and truncation rules so they never wrap awkwardly or overlap on smaller screens.
- Use `overflow: hidden` and `text-overflow: ellipsis` when forcing `white-space: nowrap` on text strings.

## 5. View Transitions & Script Lifecycles (Instant Page Loads)
- The site uses `<ClientRouter />` for SPA-like transitions and page prefetching.
- **Script Tag Rules**: All client-side scripts inside Astro pages (`.astro`) must include the `data-astro-rerun` attribute (e.g., `<script data-astro-rerun>`). This forces the script to re-initialize and bind event listeners to the new DOM elements every time the page is navigated to.
- **Global Event Listeners**: If a script attaches event listeners to global objects (`window` or `document`), always clean up previous listeners before adding new ones (e.g. by storing the listener function on the `window` object and running `removeEventListener` first) to prevent memory leaks and stacked handlers on transition re-runs.

## 6. Verification Checklist
Before finishing any change:
1. Always run a static build check (`npm run build`) to ensure Astro compiles without JSX/curly-brace syntax errors.
2. Check layout responsiveness: shrink the viewport to mobile sizes to verify that header bars, controls, and grids stack or scale cleanly without overflows or broken buttons.
